args: La la laaa â™ª\nThat was so fun!
You seem awfully happy, Sarisse.\nDid something nice happen?
Yep! I bought some amazing thread for\nsuuuuper cheap here in town.
That seems like a nice hobby.
It's pretty great, all right. But yeah,\nI can't tell you how awesome that\nvillage shopping place was.
It was full of these colorful outdoor stalls\nwhere everyone was yelling and arguing\nabout prices. So great!
Oh! That's a flea market. It's where you go\nto sell old things you don't need anymore.
Do they sell fleas? Ah ha ha! Oh man,\nI slay me. ...Oh, but wait! There's more!
Bwa ha ha! Yeah, hagglin' is the best.\nThe shopkeeps are usually reduced to\ntears when ol' Ranzal's done with 'em.
I KNOW, right? Every time they'd lower\nthe price, I'd be like, ï¼‚That is an INSULT,\nsir! Don't you know who I am?!ï¼‚
Bwaaa ha ha! I love it! Maybe we're\nmore alike than I thought.
I mean, I feel kinda bad for the shopkeeps,\nbut that's just the flea-market game!
It was a total blastâ€”and I owe it all to\nyou, {player_name}!
I'm not sure what I did here.
If I hadn't joined you and your pals,\nI never would have come to a town\nthis far from my home!
THAT'S why I owe it all to you.
Shoppin' is all well and good, but it ain't\nthe only fun thing about this town.
There's also the food. Speakin' of which,\nI know a little place you just gotta try!
Yessss! Take me, take me, take meeee!\nPleeeeeeease?
I blew all my money at the flea market.
*sniff* Guess I'll just have to go home and\neat rocks tonight. Cheap, cheap rocks...
Aw, don't be like that. It'll be my treat!
'Course! You and me got lots in common\nafter all, yeah?
Sharin' a meal is gonna be a blast.
Sarisse does have a certain way of\nbrightening the air around her.
Go ahead and enjoy your dinner, Sarisse.\nI'll let Luca know what's going on.
Ya hear that? We've been ordered to go\neat by royalty. Got no choice now.
...Ranzal, this menu is CRAZYPANTS!\nI've never heard of half this stuff!
Well then, order whatever sounds good.\nIt's all on me!
Excuse me? Waiter? We'd like to order!\nOkay, so I want this...and this...\nOh, and some of these...
(Huh. She's orderin' a whole lot'a food\nfor such a tiny kid.)
And a dozen of these... Oooo, and this!\nOh, and can I get this in a trough?\nIs that a serving size you guys do?
*BRRRP!* ...Oh my gosh, Ranzal,\nthat was the best meal ever.
I didn't think there was any way ya'd eat\nall'a that, but ya did! Nice job, kid.
Guess we should grab the bill now, yeah?
The bill? Heck no! I'm just getting started!\nI still need to try the salad, and the fish,\nand that giant haunch of meat, and...
You know what? Let's just go ahead and\norder one of everything! We'll make it\na challenge to ourselves.
You okay, Ranzal? You've gone all pale.
Well, if you're sure... Okay, time to order!\nExcuse me! Waiter!
I'm gonna be a broke joker by the time\nthis night's done...but a promise is a\npromise, so I gotta see it through!
Boy, there isn't a bad item on the menu.\nI can see why you love this place!
Wait, what's this way down here?\nThe ï¼‚Helltongue Spicy Specialï¼‚?
Yeah, I dunno if yer gonna dig that one.\nIt's more of an adult taste.
Then THIS adult is going to eat it all!
Feel free to stop eatin' that whenever,\nyeah?
You know what? I think I'm getting\nused to this.
Or else yer tongue's just gone numb.\nEither way, ya plowed through that\nlike a real grown-up. Nice job!
Woo-hoo! I did it, Ranzal!\nI ate everything on the menu!
No! I want more spice! MORE!
